## Cmake CXX Compiler output ABI  

### Note about MSYS2 ar.exe tool applied to adapt clang++ output til linker input

* NOTE on MSYS2 clang tool chain deviation from Linux counterpart
  * clang++ compiles to windows .obj files instead of Limux .a (archive) files.
  * Windows obj-files are in COFF-format while a-files are in ELF format.
  * Thus the ar.exe tool is applied between the compilation and linkage stage to create an .a-file from the object file
```
    /C/msys64/mingw64/bin/cmake.exe -E remove -f CMakeFiles/cmTC_d28e5.dir/objects.a
    /C/msys64/mingw64/bin/ar.exe cr CMakeFiles/cmTC_d28e5.dir/objects.a "CMakeFiles/cmTC_d28e5.dir/CMakeCXXCompilerABI.cpp.obj" 
```
  * The created .a-file is then provided to the linker.
  ```
      /C/msys64/mingw64/bin/clang++.exe      -v -Wl,--whole-archive CMakeFiles/cmTC_d28e5.dir/objects.a -Wl,--no-whole-archive  -o cmTC_d28e5.exe -Wl,--major-image-version,0,--minor-image-version,0   
```

  * But the Embarcadero back-end fails to link this file (it complains that it may be COFF)
```
[[CLANG-BCC]]:CreateProcess="C:\Program Files (x86)\Embarcadero\Studio\17.0\bin\bcc32c.exe" -tR -ecmTC_18743.exe -tM -lS:1048576 -lSc:4098 -lH:1048576 -lHc:8192 -v -tC -tM -Od -v CMakeFiles/cmTC_18743.dir/objects.a
```
